<td align=center>
<br>
<a name="corp"><hr width=80%></a>
<br>
<img border=0 width=220 height=34 src="images/hncn.gif" alt="Corporate News">
<br><br>
</td></tr>

<tr><td align=left>
<blockquote>

<b>BankAmerica Third Quarter Earnings</b><br>

San Francisco, 16 October       <br>    

BankAmerica Corporation reported third quarter 1996
earnings per share and net income of $1.75 and $683 million respectively,
compared with $1.72 and $704 million for the same period a year ago. Third
quarter net income includes a one-time assessment of $82 million associated with
the recapitalization of the Savings Association Insurance Fund (SAIF). Excluding
the effect of this assessment, earnings per share and net income for the third
quarter would have been $1.88 and $731 million respectively, which would
represent increases of 9 percent and 4 percent compared with the same period a
year ago. In addition, the return on average common equity for the third quarter
of 1996, excluding the SAIF assessment, would have been 15.23 percent, an
increase of 14 basis points from the same period a year ago. <br>

David A Coulter, Chairman and CEO, said "Once again, we had a very solid quarter.
Credit quality continued to improve, expenses remained under control and we began
to make progress in our efforts toward strategic redeployment of capital." <br>

Contact: Peter Magnani, San Francisco  (415) 953 2418
<br><br>


<b>More than 85,000 BankAmerica employees receive stock options </b><br>

San Francisco, 19 November          <br>  

BankAmerica implemented one of the largest and most
inclusive employee stock option programs in the world. The program, called "Take
Ownership!", is designed to award more than 85,000 employees around the world -
including most hourly and part-time workers - option to between 50 and 90 shares
of BankAmerica Corporation common stock every six months over the next three
years. "Take Ownership!" was unveiled by Chairman and CEO David Coulter in a live
satellite broadcast to employees worldwide. Coulter said that a key goal of the
program is to enhance service to Bank of America customers. <br>


<br><br>


<b> BankAmerica fourth quarter restructuring charge </b><br>

San Francisco, 12 December  <br>

BankAmerica Corporation said that it will take a
pre-tax charge of $280 million as the result of decisions to implement a number
of restructurings of its business activities. The charge will result in an
after-tax effect on net income of approximately $165 million in the fourth
quarter of 1996. <br>

David A. Coulter, Chairman and CEO said "As we have previously indicated, our
capital allocation strategy calls for ongoing review of our businesses and staff
units to find ways to operate more efficiently and to use our capital more
productively. The restructuring charge reflects the latest decisions resulting
from this on-going review process." The charge will cover severance payments,
premises and other costs in wholesale and retail banking and in staff support
areas. 

<br><br>

</blockquote>
</td></tr>

<tr>
<td align=center>
<br>
<a name="usa"><hr width=80%></a>
<br>
<img border=0 width=220 height=34 src="images/hnusa.gif" alt="American News">
<br><br>
</td></tr>



<tr><td align=left>
<blockquote>

<b> Bank of America announces enhancements to WANDA Cash Management Service Platform </b><br>
Atlanta, November 18  <br>  

Bank of America's Global Payment Services division
announced a major new release of WANDA Electronic Services, an integrated cash
management services platform that incorporates several new enhancements designed
to provide an increased range of services to corporate customers. The
announcement was made at the Treasury Management Association's 17th Annual
Treasury Management Conference, where the platform was demonstrated. Introduced
in 1994, WANDA provides a Windows-based, single point of access to a full range
of Bank of America cash management and foreign exchange services through modular
applications that plug into the WANDA platform. 

<br><br>

</blockquote>
</td></tr>



<tr>
<td align=center>
<br>
<a name="asia"><hr width=80%></a>
<br>
<img border=0 width=220 height=34 src="images/hnasia.gif" alt="Asia News">
<br><br>
</td></tr>

<tr><td align=left>
<blockquote>

<b>Far Eastern Bank, Bank of America sign twinning agreement</b><br>

4 September, Vladivostok        <br>        

Vladivostok-based Far-Eastern Bank and Bank of America today signed a two year, $3 million, World
Bank twinning agreement, the first of its kind for Russia with a US
bank.  The twinning program is part of the World Bank's Financial
Institutions Development Project (FIDP), which was introduced in 1993
to improve Russia's banking services and stability, help utilise its
financial resources more efficiently, and improve its access to
international finance.<br>

Contact:        Nerys Williams, Hong Kong       (8522) 597 3389<br>


<br><br>

<b>Bank of America Appointed Advisor for Major Power Project in Taiwan</b><br>

25 September, Hong Kong     <br>    

Bank of America has been named as financial advisor for a major US$650 million independent power project
in Taoyuan County, Taiwan.  The 2x450 megawatt combined cycle gas
turbine powered plant will be located along the coast in the Keng Tze
Kou section of Lu Chu Township.<br>

Contact: Nerys Williams, Hong Kong (8522) 597 3389<br>


</blockquote>
</td></tr>

<tr>
<td align=center>
<br>
<a name="europe"><hr width=80%></a>
<br>
<img border=0 width=220 height=34 src="images/hneec.gif" alt="Europe News">
<br><br>
</td></tr>

<tr><td align=left>
<blockquote>

<b>Bank of America appoints new head for Europe, Middle East & Africa  </b><br>

London, 17 December  <br>

P. Gerald Doherty, Group Executive Vice President at Bank
of America has been named to head the bank's Europe, Middle East & Africa (EMEA)
Group in addition to his current responsibilities as head of the bank's Global
Capital Markets Group. He will be based in London. Mr. Doherty succeeds Ralph C.
Schauss, Group Executive Vice President, who will head EMEA Emerging Markets,
responsible for the bank's existing business and expansion in these markets. 

<br>

Contact:        Susan Grice, London  (171) 634 4770<br>


<br><br>


</blockquote>
</td></tr>

