Title:  EMWL: Pakistan Board of Investment
</DOCHDR>

<HTML> <!--created Oyster Systems--> <!--May 1996--> <HEAD> <TITLE> EMWL:
Pakistan Board of Investment </TITLE> </HEAD>

<body bgcolor="FFFFCE" vlink="311063" text="000000" link="311063">

<center> <font size=3>

<table border=0> <tr> <td align=right> <nobr> <a href="../../../index.html"
name="top"><img border=0 hspace=0 src="../images/spon1.gif"></a> </nobr> </td>
</tr>

<tr> <td align=middle> <img src="images/spon96001.gif"> <H1>Pakistan</H1>
<H4><i>Poised for Progress</i></H4> <H3>BOARD OF INVESTMENT</H3>

</td> </tr>

<tr> <td align=left> <blockquote>



<HTML> <HEAD><TITLE>BOI News Letter</TITLE></HEAD> <BODY>

<P> The Board of Investment is the focal point of contact between potential investors and all
government agencies concerned with investments and is responsible for providing
advice to the government, formulating investment policies as well as providing
advice to investors and extending all necessary support to an investor for
expeditious completion of his project.

<P> The Board of Investment is an investment promotion and facilitation agency
working directly under the Prime Minister. The Board is headed by the Prime
Minister and plays a pivotal role in the formulation of investment policies and
investor facilitation. It includes all Ministers -in-charge of economic
ministries, the Governor of the Central Bank and the Chairman of the Pakistan
Banking Council.

<P> The Board provides all the necessary information to potential investors, both
domestic and foreign and assists investors in expeditious processing and
implementation of their investment proposals and in coordinating with other
government departments. The Board can advise on foreign exchange controls,
regulations governing foreign investment, the payment of royalties and work
permit restrictions and any other aspect relating to direct investment in
business and industry anywhere in the country.

<P> The Board is responsible for a number of significant fiscal and monetary
incentive schemes which it has designed to facilitate direct investment in
priority areas.

<P> The Board of Investment has prepared a number of pre-feasibility studies
in respect of such projects where a large investment potential exists. The Board
of Investment has also designed an investors' guide, which is available in English,
Arabic, French, German, Italian, Chinese, Italian, Chinese, Korean and Japanese
language.

<P ALIGN="CENTER"> <B><U>Contact BOI for more information on these or any other
matter.</U></B>

<P ALIGN="CENTER"> <B>BOARD OF INVESTMENT</B><BR>

<ALIGN="CENTER"> <B>GOVERNMENT OF PAKISTAN</B><BR>

<ALIGN="CENTER"> <B>12-13th Floor, Saudi Pak Tower, Jinnah Avenue</B><BR>

<ALIGN="CENTER"> <B>Islamabad, Pakistan</B><BR>

<ALIGN="CENTER"> <B>TEL: (92-51) 9221826</B><BR>

<ALIGN="CENTER"> <B>FAX: (92-51) 9215554, 9217665, 9203281</B><BR>

<center>
<br>For more information, click on the colored text:<br><br>

<font size=3>
<nobr>
<b>
<a href="spon96001.html"> [ BOI Home ] </a><br>
<a href="spon96001.1.html"> [ About the BOI ] </a><br>
<a href="spon96001.2.html"> [ Pakistan - Macro Economic Indicators ] </a><br>
<a href="spon96001.3.html"> [ General rules governing foreign investment ] </a><br>
<a href="spon96001.4.html"> [ List of pre-feasibility studies available with BOI ] </a><br>
<a href="spon96001.5.html"> [ BOI Newsletter ] </a>
</nobr>
</b>
<br><br><br>


</font>
</blockquote>
</td>
</tr>

</font>
</blockquote> </td> </tr>

</table>

