<HTML> <!--created Oyster Systems--> <!--May 1996--> <HEAD> <TITLE> EMWL:
Pakistan Board of Investment </TITLE> </HEAD>

<body bgcolor="FFFFCE" vlink="311063" text="000000" link="311063">

<center> <font size=3>

<table border=0> <tr> <td align=right> <nobr> <a href="../../../index.html"
name="top"><img border=0 hspace=0 src="../images/spon1.gif"></a> </nobr> </td>
</tr>

<tr> <td align=middle> <img src="images/spon96001.gif"> <H1>Pakistan</H1>
<H4><i>Poised for Progress</i></H4> <H3><b>BOI'S NEWS LETTER</b></H3>
</td> </tr>

<tr> <td align=left> <blockquote>



<HTML> <HEAD><TITLE>BOI News Letter</TITLE></HEAD> <BODY>


<P>

<H3> <B>Foreign Direct Investment in Pakistan doubled during 1995-96 over last
year (1994-95)<I><U><BR> </U></I></B> </H3> <P> Because of hassle free and investor friendly
Policies of the Government of Pakistan, the Total Foreign Direct Investment (FDI)
into Pakistan during the 1995-96 has more than doubled as compared to last year. Total
FDI during July 1995 to June, 1996 is US $1,097 million while during July 1994 
to June 1995, total FDI was US $442.4 million.

<H3> <B>World's largest Power Station in private sector<I><U><BR>
</U></I></B> </H3> <P> The Hub Power Project is the world's largest power station
 in private sector, has a total capacity of 1292 MW. The project, under trial production since July, 1996 with
 one generator, would start generation at full capacity in March, 1997. It is being built at a
 total cost of US $1.6 billion.

<H3> <B>Italian Investments in Larkana<I><U><BR> </U></I></B>
</H3> <P> M/S Capello Tubi, and Olmia Consortium, Italian Conglomerates, in joint
collaboration with Pakistan Industrial Development Corporation, (PIDC) are investing
respectively in a Rice processing project and steel pipe manufacture unit at Larkana.
Total cost for each project is project is estimated at US $18.00 million and US $51.00 million
respectivley.

<H3> <B>Korean Investors Visit Pakistan<I><U><BR>
</U></I></B> </H3> <P> As follow up of the successful Pakistan Investment Conference, held in July, 1996
at seoul, Korea, Leading Korean Corporations, Daewoo, Hyundai and Lucky Gold, have
sent high powered delegations to Pakistan. After visiting various site, and in-depth
meetings with senior officials, these Corporations evinced keen interest, in port
development, Petro-Chemicals, Telecommunications, Oil and Gas projects etc.

<H3> <B>Investment in Power Sector<BR> </B> </H3> <P> As a result of Highly Competitive and investor-friendly regime
of PAKISTAN around eighteen MNCs have plan to install power houses with total generating capacity of
3530 MWs. They have achieved the financial close and the projects would be commissioned by Dec, 1998.


<P>
<BR>
<P>


