<HTML>
<!--created Oyster Systems-->
<!--May 1996-->
<HEAD>
<TITLE>
EMWL: IBC Information on Attending
</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<body background="images/backgd.gif" bgcolor="ff6600" vlink="CCCCCC" alink="ff6600" text="000000" link="FFFFFF">

<table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%>
<tr><td valign=top align=left>

<img border=0 width=72 height=247 src="images/sidetop.gif" alt="Graphic"><br><a href="intro.html"><img border=0 width=72 height=19 src="images/side1.gif" alt="Introduction"></a><br><a href="attend.html"><img border=0 width=72 height=20 src="images/side2.gif" alt="Attending"></a><br><a href="spon.html"><img border=0 width=72 height=20 src="images/side3.gif" alt="Sponsors"></a><br><a href="agend.html"><img border=0 width=72 height=20 src="images/side4.gif" alt="Agenda"></a><br><a href="exhibit.html"><img border=0 width=72 height=20 src="images/side5.gif" alt="Exhibiting"></a><br><a href="history.html"><img border=0 width=72 height=20 src="images/side6.gif" alt="History"></a><br><a href="more.html"><img border=0 width=72 height=21 src="images/side7.gif" alt="More Info"></a><br><a href="more.html"><img border=0 width=72 height=21 src="images/side9.gif" alt="Register"></a><br><a href="index.html"><img border=0 width=72 height=21 src="images/side8.gif" alt="Home"></a><br><br>

</td> 

<td>

<center>
<img  width=363 height=38 border=0 hspace=0 src="images/title2.gif" alt="Attending">
</center>
<br><br>
<blockquote>
<ul>
The International Bond Congress is a unique event in the financial calendar.  It provides an opportunity for all fixed income professionals - investors, issuers, salesforces, traders, economists, analysts, origination and syndication officials and information providers - to come together for two days in London to discuss developments in the bond markets.
<br><br>
The International Bond Congress has become the premier event of its kind.  Over 5,000 delegates have attended the previous two congresses in October 1994 and September 1995, representing the broadest possible spectrum of bond market participants.
<br><br>
The combination of a conference - with top name plenary speakers, panel discussions and workshops - together with an Expo with dedicated stands, hospitality suites and meeting areas, gives delegates the opportunity not only to benefit from in-depth analysis of bond market trends but also to meet an unrivalled gathering of clients, potential clients and peers in an informal environment.
<br><br>
With the experience gained from the previous congresses, this year's event - to take place on Tuesday 25 and Wednesday 26 February 1997 - promises to be the most successful to date.  The venue will be the Queen Elizabeth II Conference Centre, London.
<br><br>
The Congress will also offer bond market professionals the chance to help set the agenda in what promises to be one of the most exciting and challenging eras in the history of the fixed income markets.  The range of products available to portfolio managers is growing all the time - for example credit derivatives, repos and strips - and investors are increasingly turning towards higher-yielding paper from corporates and emerging markets as interest rates remain at historic lows. 
<br><br>
The biggest potential change to the bond markets of all - European Monetary Union - looms ever larger.  Less than two years away from the date of the Congress Europes bond markets may change for ever.
<br><br>
These issues will be explained in detail in the workshops and also in panel discussions involving leading economists, issuers, traders, regulators and investors.
<br><br></ul>
<font size=4><b>The Conference</b></font>
<ul>
Delegates will have full access to all the speeches and workshops on both days of the conference.  The conference consists of three plenary sessions, with a keynote address and panel discussions on both mornings and a further panel discussion on the first afternoon, as well as a closing address on the second afternoon.
<br><br>
After each morning plenary session the Conference will split into streams of four parallel workshops which will cover specific market topics, together with a fifth stream on information technology services.  There will be a total of 32 sponsors' workshops.  Each presentation will last for 50 minutes enabling speakers to provide comprehensive coverage of their subjects.
<br><br></ul>
<font size=4><b>The Exhibition</b></font>
<ul>
The major suppliers to the bond market will exhibit their products and services at the Congress.  As well as sponsoring institutions these will include information, systems and software providers, credit rating agencies, clearing services, risk management experts and futures and options exchanges.  It provides an opportunity to try out many of the products and gain first-hand experience.
<br><br></ul>
<font size=4><b>Private Meetings</b></font>
<ul>
Many of the sponsors will be holding private meetings for delegates with leading economists and strategists, members of central banks, debt offices, ministries of finance and borrowers in their hospitality suites.  In addition to these meetings, the suites offer an excellent opportunity to welcome existing and new counterparties.  It provides an excellent opportunity to learn about new markets and the services offered by the sponsors.
<br><br></ul>
<font size=4><b>To Register</b></font>
<ul>
<b>Conference & Exhibition</b><br>
Fee-paying delegates will have access to both the conference and exhibition, as well as to the central meeting areas, refreshments, documentation and a cocktail reception at the end of the first evening.  The cost is 495 + VAT for delegates registering before December 13 and 595 + VAT thereafter.
<br><br>
<b>However, fixed-income investors will be able to attend both the conference and exhibition as complimentary guests of the sponsors.</b>
<br><br>
<b>Exhibition Only </b><br>
Pre-registered visitors can visit the exhibition and hospitality suites, giving them the opportunity to meet counterparties and potential clients or learn more about the sponsoring and exhibiting institutions.  Exhibition visitors will also have refreshments and will be invited to the cocktail reception at the end of the first evening but will not have access to the conference sessions.
</ul><br>

[ <a href="more.html">Click here for more information on attending</a> ]<br>

</blockquote>

</td></tr></table>

<center>

