<HTML>
<!--created Oyster Systems-->
<!--May 1996-->
<HEAD>
<TITLE>
EMWL: IBC Sponsoring and Exhibiting
</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<body background="images/backgd.gif" bgcolor="ff6600" vlink="CCCCCC" alink="ff6600" text="000000" link="FFFFFF">

<table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%>
<tr><td valign=top align=left>

<img border=0 width=72 height=247 src="images/sidetop.gif" alt="Graphic"><br><a href="intro.html"><img border=0 width=72 height=19 src="images/side1.gif" alt="Introduction"></a><br><a href="attend.html"><img border=0 width=72 height=20 src="images/side2.gif" alt="Attending"></a><br><a href="spon.html"><img border=0 width=72 height=20 src="images/side3.gif" alt="Sponsors"></a><br><a href="agend.html"><img border=0 width=72 height=20 src="images/side4.gif" alt="Agenda"></a><br><a href="exhibit.html"><img border=0 width=72 height=20 src="images/side5.gif" alt="Exhibiting"></a><br><a href="history.html"><img border=0 width=72 height=20 src="images/side6.gif" alt="History"></a><br><a href="more.html"><img border=0 width=72 height=21 src="images/side7.gif" alt="More Info"></a><br><a href="more.html"><img border=0 width=72 height=21 src="images/side9.gif" alt="Register"></a><br><a href="index.html"><img border=0 width=72 height=21 src="images/side8.gif" alt="Home"></a><br><br>

</td> 

<td>

<center>
<img  width=363 height=38 border=0 hspace=0 src="images/title5.gif" alt="Exhibiting">
</center>
<br><br>
<blockquote>
<font size=4><b>By Industry</b></font>
<ul>
The following industries and fields were represented at the Congress:
<br><br>
<table border=0>
<tr><td>
International Bond Markets<br>
Bond Market Analytics<br>
Money Market Services<br>
 and Instruments<br>
Futures and Options Exchanges<br>
Global Custody<br>
 and Clearing Services<br>
Portfolio Techniques<br>
Independent Economists<br>
Information Providers<br>
Credit Rating Agencies<br>
</td><td>
Applied Derivatives<br>
Legal Services<br>
Bond Insurance<br>
Publishers<br>
Repos Services<br>
Risk Management<br>
Trading<br>
Performance Measurement<br>
Security Printers<br>
Computer Software<br>
</td></tr>
</table>

<br></ul>
<font size=4><b>By Country</b></font>
<ul>
Companies from twenty-one countries have participated in the Congress, taking either a hospitality suite or an exhibition stand.
<br><br></ul>
<font size=4><b>By Company</b></font>
<ul>
Over 130 companies have sponsored or exhibited at the International Bond Congress.
<br><br></ul>
<font size=4><b>Attendance in 1997</b></font>
<ul>
<b>Complimentary Access to the Congress</b><br>
Complimentary places will be provided to each sponsor to enable their clients and potential clients to attend the Congress free of charge.
<br><br>
<b>Interchangeable Privilege Passes for the Congress</b><br>
Interchangeable passes will permit sponsors' and exhibitors' personnel access to the entire Congress.
Numbers of complimentary and interchangeable passes will vary according to the level of sponsorship.
<br><br>
<b>Free Entry to the Expo</b><br>
Invitations will be prepared and mailed by Euromoney on behalf of the sponsors or exhibitors. This provides the opportunity to invite clients as well as potential clients to the Expo free of charge.
<br><br>
<b>Congress Delegates</b><br>
Apart from the sponsors' and exhibitors' personal invitations, Euromoney will also print a brochure for the event to attract fee paying delegates. This brochure will be mailed worldwide to people of the right calibre from appropriate institutions.

<br><br></ul>
<font size=4><b>Visitors and Delegates</b></font>
<ul>
5,000 delegates and visitors have attended the two previous Congresses.
<br><br>
<b>By Region</b>
<br>
<img width=333 height=183 src="images/region.gif">
<br><br>
<b>By Industry</b>
<br>
<img width=333 height=183 src="images/industry.gif">
<br><br></ul>
<font size=4><b>Marketing and Advertising</b></font>
<ul>
Advertisements announcing the Congress will appear in a variety of Euromoney and other publications. It will also be promoted evidently via the Internet which provides the event with a global, 24-hour information and registration service. Euromoney will use its extensive in-house database and research new lists to market the Congress directly to targeted individuals.

<br><br>
</ul></ul>
</blockquote>

</td></tr></table>

