<!--May 1996-->
<HEAD>
<TITLE>
EMWL: IBC Historical Information
</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<body background="images/backgd.gif" bgcolor="ff6600" vlink="CCCCCC" alink="ff6600" text="000000" link="FFFFFF">

<table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%>
<tr><td valign=top align=left>

<img border=0 width=72 height=247 src="images/sidetop.gif" alt="Graphic"><br><a href="intro.html"><img border=0 width=72 height=19 src="images/side1.gif" alt="Introduction"></a><br><a href="attend.html"><img border=0 width=72 height=20 src="images/side2.gif" alt="Attending"></a><br><a href="spon.html"><img border=0 width=72 height=20 src="images/side3.gif" alt="Sponsors"></a><br><a href="agend.html"><img border=0 width=72 height=20 src="images/side4.gif" alt="Agenda"></a><br><a href="exhibit.html"><img border=0 width=72 height=20 src="images/side5.gif" alt="Exhibiting"></a><br><a href="history.html"><img border=0 width=72 height=20 src="images/side6.gif" alt="History"></a><br><a href="more.html"><img border=0 width=72 height=21 src="images/side7.gif" alt="More Info"></a><br><a href="more.html"><img border=0 width=72 height=21 src="images/side9.gif" alt="Register"></a><br><a href="index.html"><img border=0 width=72 height=21 src="images/side8.gif" alt="Home"></a><br><br>

</td> 

<td>

<center>
<img  width=363 height=38 border=0 hspace=0 src="images/title6.gif" alt="History">
</center>
<br><br>
<blockquote>
<font size=4><b>The 1995 Event</b></font>
<ul>
The Second Euromoney International Bond Congress staged at the Barbican, London, attracted 2,650 attendees from 50 different countries.
<br><br>
The conference featured three plenary speakers Urban Backstrom, Michael Bloomberg and Sir Alan Walters. The keynote speakers included Desmond Fitzgerald, Gerald Holtham, Giles Keating and Eduardo Schwartz.
<br><br>
Sponsors and exhibitors who participated in the Expo reported many new, high quality contacts and excellent business leads. Exhibiting companies made use of this high profile event to launch new products and services, as well as a means to gain important exposure for their particular areas of expertise. Bloomberg coincided the introduction of their new 'Open' system with the event. Merita Bank used the event as a launch pad for their new corporate name. Some companies used the marketing potential of their stands to the full; Nordbanken, for example, organised a television and press conference with Urban Backstrom - the Governor of the Swedish Central Bank.
<br><br>
The Expo has clearly become an excellent opportunity to meet the key players in the market as well as being the vehicle for pursuing a range of business and marketing objectives - launching products, instruments and services, increasing corporate awareness and investigating new markets.
<br><br></ul>
</blockquote>

</td></tr></table>

