<center>
<h2>
NETWORK
</h2>
<h4>More details: <a href="http://www.gbank.be">http://www.gbank.be/</h4></a>
</center>

<BR>

<blockquote>

<h3>Europe:</h3>
Generale Bank has developed a dense network in the <b>Benelux countries:</b> Generale Bank <b>Belgium</b> (1,100 branches), Banque Generale du <b>Luxembourg</b> (48 branches), Generale Bank <b>Nederland</b> (90 branches).
Generale Bank also has a strong presence in <b>France</b> via its wholly-owned subsidiary, Banque Parisienne de Credit (88 branches). It is also present in Germany (6 branches), Spain (4 branches), Portugal (2 branches), UK (3 branches), Italy (Milan), The Channel Islands and Switzerland. It has Representative Offices in Istanbul, Moscow and Prague.
<br>
<br>
<h3>Africa:</h3> 
Mostly via <b>Belgolaise Bank</b>, Generale Bank is present in Burkina-Faso, Burundi, Congo, Ghana, Guinea, Ivory Coast, Kenya, Mauritania, Niger, Nigeria, Rwanda, Senegal, South Africa, Tanzania, Togo, Uganda and Zaire.
<br>
<br>
<h3>Asia:</h3>
Generale Bank has a strong presence in <b>Hong Kong</b> via Generale Belgian Bank (28 branches). It has Representative Offices in the People's Republic of China (Beijing, Shanghai and Guangzhou), India, Indonesia, Iran, Japan, Taiwan, Thailand and Vietnam.
<br>
<br>
<h3>America:</h3>
Generale Bank has a branch in New York and Representative Offices in Brazil and Mexico.

</blockquote>

<BR>
<BR>
