<TD>

<center>
<img align=center src="banner.gif">
</center>

<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<BR>

<center>
<h2>
INTERNATIONAL STRATEGY
</h2>
</center>

<BR>

<blockquote>

<ul>
<li> Changing from being a Belgian bank with branches abroad to being a European bank with its roots in Belgium.
<li> From its base in Belgium, further developing its geographical diversity according to the requirements of its customers, who are becoming active further afield.
<li> Being active within a 400 kilometre radius of Brussels, concentrating more particularly on services to SMEs and wealthy individual customers.
<li> In Hong Kong, adopting an international strategy similar to that used in Europe, so as to cover the needs of the local customers in this area of Asia.
<li> Strengthening its presence in Africa via the Belgolaise Bank and its subsidiaries.
<li> Becoming a Euro clearing bank with full service to the banks outside the Economic and Monetary Union (Emu) as from 1 January 1999.

</blockquote>

<BR>
<BR>
