<a href="wl.96.05.8.html"><b>FROM THE EDITOR </b></a>

<BR> Business leaders are aware that image counts. They must convince staff that
growth and loyalty are on the agenda<BR>
<BR>

<a href="wl.96.05.9.html"><b>COMMENT </b></a>
<BR>
 Makarand Dehejia contends that the multilateral institutions need to change
their de&THORN;nition of success in order to link development and sound
&THORN;nance<BR>
<BR>

<a href="wl.96.05.10.html"><b>SACHS ON COMPETITIVENESS </b></a>
<BR>
 Jeffrey Sachs writes that once-laggard giant economies such as Brazil and
Russia are beginning to return to life
<BR>
<BR>

<a href="wl.96.05.11.html"><b> WORLD ECONOMIC FORUM </b></a>

<br> Global growth companies explained, plus highlights of recent meeting and
details of forthcoming summits
<BR>
<BR>

<a href="wl.96.05.12.html"><b> REVIEW </b></a>
